<TITLE> Dhaka rounds of Astro Olympiad start </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 3 (bdnews24.com)The selection round of the Dhaka divisional contestants of the 'bdnews24.com Fifth Astro Olympiad  2010' began on Saturday. The written exam was held from 8am to 11am at Saint Joseph High School. The selection will be completed after the analytical ability exam being held on Sunday at the National Science and Technology Institute in Agargaon. "Over 100 contestants, in two age groups of 14-16 and 17-19, took part in the exam," said Moshurl Amin, general secretary of the national committee for the Astro-Olympiad. With the sponsorship of bdnews24.com, the countrywide competition has been organised by the Bangladesh Astronomy Olympiad National Committee and the Astronomical Association. This competition is being held to encourage the study of astronomy amongst students. 78 participants have so far won through from the divisional contests in Chittagong, Rajshahi, Barisal, Sylhet and Rangpur divisions. 17 candidates from Chittagong, 19 from Rajshahi, 12 from Barisal, 20 from Sylhet, 10 from Rangpur, and 30 from Khulna will take now part in the national level final taking place on Apr 9. The top two winners will be sent to participate in the 'International Astronomy and Astrophysics Olympiad-2010' to be held in Beijing. They will also participate in the 15th International Astronomy Olympiad in Ukraine and the 6th International Asia-Pacific Astronomy Olympiad  2010 in Indonesia. b
